This is my remembrance of the days leading up to the bin Laden raid, the day of the raid centered on the iconic Situation Room photograph, and the day after.⁣
⁣
Note that the most important people from this day are not pictured at all. Our country owes a debt of gratitude to Admiral Bill McRaven, the former Commander of Special Operations, and the members of SEAL Team Six that planned for and executed the mission. They are the real heroes of this day. It was a real honor to be at Fort Campbell a few days later when they presented President Obama with the American flag that flew aboard the helicopter.⁣
⁣
If you have more questions, please leave them in the comments section. I will try to answer the ones that I can. I will not be able to respond to questions about what was on the screen during the raid or what I might have overheard.⁣
⁣
Please stay safe, practice social distancing, and wear a mask when you’re out and about!⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣

Two weeks ago, I had the chance to discuss some of my photographs with Michael Shaw and Cara Finnegan of Chatting the Pictures. The program is produced by the visual and media literacy organization, Reading the Pictures. Here is the last part of the program looking at presidential leadership in a health crisis. We discussed one of my contact sheets from President Reagan’s visit to the National Institute of Health. The appearance took place during the AIDS epidemic on July 23, 1987, and it featured Reagan holding a baby that had the virus. 
Follow @readingthepictures on Instagram.

node.text:
I had the chance to discuss some of my photographs with Michael Shaw and Cara Finnegan of Chatting the Pictures. ⁣
⁣
Here is Part 2 of a 3-part program looking at presidential leadership in a health crisis. ⁣
⁣
In this photo, taken October 10, 2011, President Obama walks into a hospital room at Walter Reed National Military Medical Center in Bethesda, Md., where he presented a wounded warrior with a Purple Heart.⁣
⁣
The program is produced by the visual and media literacy non-profit, Reading the Pictures. ⁣
⁣
Follow @readingthepictures on Instagram.⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
